repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Uses the `PyMonitoring` C-API that is being developed for Py3.13.

See https://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.monitoring.html
See https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/111997
See https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/116413

commit.message: Implement PEP-669 sys.monitoring support.
Fix macro signatures and add missing dummy macros.
Fix long lines.
Test runner: Use tag instead of  >version to exclude pstats tests only on Python 3.12, not later.
Re-add dummy macro in Py3.12.
Make macro implementation safer.
Start implementing generator tracing.
Fix compilation.
Trace coroutine resumes as function start in non-monitoring Python.

Fix code object creation for Lambda nodes.
This needs to be done after initialising the scope since we need to know the local scope to correctly include args and kwargs.
Disable coverage/tracing tests in Py3.12.
Fix fallback declaration.
Generally disable monitoring/tracing tests in non-CPython before Py3.13 (not only PyPy).
Implement monitoring for generators and fix return value reporting.
Implement exception monitoring and remove the code in pre-monitoring Python versions since it was never actually used.

Fix 'skip_dispatch' condition for module level cpdef functions.
This was previously always off because it incorrectly reversed the "lookup_module_cpdef" option.
Remove duplicate test code.
Move import into doctest.
Let the Python cpdef wrapper function use the same code object as the underlying implementation function but do not re-initialise the trace so that both run in the same monitoring context.
Fix 'return' tracing when only 'linetrace' is enabled.
Add Python comparison test to "line_trace" test.
Do not issue start/line/return events from cpdef wrapper.
Do not generate dead code in Python cpdef wrapper.
Enable line tracing for 'pass' statements.
Implement line monitoring, including repeated line events for the loop header.
Delete test that is now invalid.
Fix PassStatNode replacement.
Make "line_trace" test failures easier to understand.
Undo accidentally committed changes.
Re-add Return tracing in the exception case for pre-monitoring profiling.
Improve test output.
Extract common code from __Pyx_TraceLine() macro to reduce the inline code overhead.
Fix some code issues with generators.

Clean up the ownership of code objects between functions, their def/cpdef wrappers, and generator def/body. The code object is now owned by the innermost tree node (wrapper/gbody/etc.) and used by the outer syntax node (lambda, generator expression, function).
Extend the generator monitoring tests.
Initial attempts to monitor fused functions and set up their code objects independently (because they are really separate functions in the same code section).
Properly apply declaration analysis to code objects.
Improve test name output by including the file extension (py/pyx/srctree)
Fix crash in error case due to invalid tree structure.
Clean up various issues with missing or mishandled code objects. We now always treat them as constant and just make sure they have their result code set up.
Use correct code object for fused wrapper functions.
Give all CFuncDefNodes a CodeObjectNode, not just those with a Python wrapper.
Use the code object of the (user facing) generator function also for the generator body (instead of the other way round) since the body has a different signature.
Implement support for STOP_ITERATION events, but do not use it for now since it's difficult to find the few cases where CPython triggers it.
Fix compilation when line tracing is disabled.
Properly exclude 'line_trace' test in Py3.12.
Rename a test file that really only represents a compile test, not an actual tracing test.
Make test more debuggable.
Merge branch 'master' into monitoring
